name: MUTO VOL.8 — TEDD MOHER (Collector's Edition)
description:
Autumn/Winter 2012

_

This 8th issue of MUTO Manifesto is a tribute to the iconic COLT Studio of the 70's, created by visionary Jim French, presenting shots of an ideal yet fictional star of this golden age. With only 50 copies in production, the Collector's Edition features a special DVD with a 6-minute video called THE LOST AUDITION OF TEDD MOHER, the first moving images ever shot by the EXTERFACE studio, as well as a limited and signed print inside, all coming in a translucent and red metallic envelope.

Special thanks to Slick It Up, Nasty Pig, Kyle King, Charlie by Matthew Zink

-

210 x 315 mm (8.27 x 12.40")
RePrint Deluxe 170g / 115g
54 pages (full color and black & white)
French-English bilingual
Printed in France

name: THE X FACES OF FRED FAURTIN
description:
2009

A special and unique signed project.

Imagined by Exterface, 'X' is a ten-acts work of art and the result of ten months working on themes such as seduction and conquest. On more than a hundred of pictures, the duet direct Fred Faurtin, through ten characters, with surprising and captivating women and men and special co-stars as François Sagat and Vin Costes. All together, they experience an emotional journey, cover and undercover, travel through times and locations where baroque, romanticism, fantastic, thriller, punk and even antiquity are intertwined.

_

245 x 305 mm (9.65 x 12")
128 pages (full color and black & white)
Glossy paper
English
Printed in Spain

name: THE THING HE LOVES
description:
Archive (2008)

Rare signed Exterface first monography.

'Intoxicatingly heady scenes, fascinating in their complexity, are bathed in sultry colors, so superlative in their execution, it’s impossible to imagine them more vivid. With Exterface’s first work of photography, The Thing He Loves, it is not the individual images themselves that will impress you most, but rather the intelligent way the photographs are composed into series. The images speak to our innermost desires. The models present themselves as in a peepshow, are close and yet at the same time vulnerable, just out of reach, making for surprisingly sensual photography.'

_

'The creative duo behind Exterface is a combination of beauty and indecency ... with a little inspiration from Bruce Weber thrown in.' Albert Smith / advocate.com

_

235 x 175 mm (9.25 x 6.9")
80 pages (full color and black & white)
English
Printed in Germany
